                            <comment id="15720082" author="iamaleksey" created="Sun, 4 Dec 2016 15:02:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Given that you&apos;ve chosen the same gc gs for all 3 tables, why not move the override to &lt;tt&gt;compile()&lt;/tt&gt; method itself?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15720328" author="jjirsa" created="Sun, 4 Dec 2016 17:57:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thought was future tables may want a different value, but that seems unlikely, and I&apos;ll make that their problem.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Force pushed - want to glance at the NEWS.txt entry as well?&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="15720415" author="iamaleksey" created="Sun, 4 Dec 2016 19:02:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t think the NEWS.txt entry is necessary here. But use your judgement. Other than that, +1.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15720676" author="jjirsa" created="Sun, 4 Dec 2016 21:59:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Aleksey. Committed without NEWS.txt in &lt;tt&gt;36a3ba0d0bd58e7fc48896557cb33caa4ae5f73f&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
